'''弗拉基米爾·普京的公眾形象'''，是指現任[[俄羅斯總統|俄羅斯總統]][[弗拉基米爾·弗拉基米羅維奇·普京|弗拉基米爾·弗拉基米羅維奇·普京]]在俄羅斯國內和世界各地的形象。

== 民意調查 ==
非政府機構[[列瓦達中心|列瓦達中心]]於2007年6月進行的民意調查顯示，普京的支持率是81%<ref>{{cite news|author=Dmitry Sudakov|title=Vladimir Putin’s trademark begins to decline|url=http://english.pravda.ru/russia/kremlin/25-01-2008/103661-putin_medvedev-0/|date=2008-01-25|accessdate=2014-08-05|archive-date=2014-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809201303/http://english.pravda.ru/russia/kremlin/25-01-2008/103661-putin_medvedev-0/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，是該段時期世界上民望最高的領導人<ref>{{cite news|last=Madslien|first=Jorn|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/business/6265068.stm|title=Russia's economic might: spooky or soothing?|publisher=BBC News|date=4 July 2007|accessdate=2010-03-02|archive-date=2009-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090111110740/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/business/6265068.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>；據全俄輿情研究中心於2012年的調查，在俄國人心中，普京的聲望高於20世紀以來[[俄國|俄國]]、[[蘇聯|蘇聯]]其他領袖<ref>{{cite web|title=«ИДЕАЛЬНЫЙ ПРАВИТЕЛЬ ДЛЯ РОССИИ - ВЧЕРА И СЕГОДНЯ»|url=http://wciom.ru/index.php?id=459&uid=112381|work=2012-02-02|accessdate=2014-08-08|archive-date=2014-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808224230/http://wciom.ru/index.php?id=459&uid=112381|dead-url=no}}</ref>。普京支持率在他的第一個總統任期內從來沒有跌破65%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.russiavotes.org/president/putin_performance_trends.php|title=Putin's performance in office — Trends|publisher=Russiavotes.org|date=31 October 2007|accessdate=2010-03-02|archive-date=2010-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100915223040/http://www.russiavotes.org/president/putin_performance_trends.php|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，但在2013年1月，他的支持率下滑至62%，是自2000年以來的最低點<ref>{{cite web |last=Arkhipov |first=Ilya |url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-24/putin-approval-rating-falls-to-lowest-since-2000-poll.html |title=Putin Approval Rating Falls to Lowest Since 2000: Poll |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2013-01-24 |accessdate=2013-06-22 |archive-date=2013-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526065400/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-24/putin-approval-rating-falls-to-lowest-since-2000-poll.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>；觀察家認為，普京的高支持率是因為他擔任總統期間俄羅斯的生活水平顯著改善，又在世界舞台上重新抬頭<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oprosy.info/news.php?extend.25 |title=Quarter of Russians Think Living Standards Improved During Putin's Rule |language=ru |publisher=Oprosy.info |date= |accessdate=2013-06-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130731141629/http://www.oprosy.info/news.php?extend.25 |archivedate=2013-07-31 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Norman Stone |title=No wonder they like Putin |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/comment/columnists/guest_contributors/article2994651.ece |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100525073652/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/comment/columnists/guest_contributors/article2994651.ece |archivedate=2010-05-25 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>，亦有分析認為，普京的受歡迎程度是歸因於部分國有或國營的電視台<ref name="Opendem"/>。

由美國和列瓦達中心在俄羅斯各地2006年6－7月的聯合調查顯示<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.levada.ru/eng/opisanie.html |title=Levada-Center -Description |publisher=Levada.ru |accessdate=2010-03-02 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20071026142155/http://www.levada.ru/eng/opisanie.html |archivedate=2007-10-26 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>，世界輿論指出無論是俄羅斯還是美國民眾，也相信俄羅斯正朝著一個反民主的方向，但俄羅斯人普遍支持普京和他的團隊的政治進程<ref name=wpo_org_g8>[http://www.worldpublicopinion.org/pipa/articles/breuropera/224.php?nid=&id=&pnt=224&lb=breu Russians Support Putin's Re-Nationalization of Oil, Control of Media, But See Democratic Future] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528012557/http://www.worldpublicopinion.org/pipa/articles/breuropera/224.php?nid=&id=&pnt=224&lb=breu |date=2015-05-28 }} – World Public Opinion.org</ref>。2005年的一項調查顯示，俄羅斯人認為該國在普京的統治下比[[葉利欽|葉利欽]]和[[戈爾巴喬夫|戈爾巴喬夫]]年代更民主，人權思想亦更好<ref name="Opendem">[http://www.npetro.net/resources/opendemocracy.pdf Russia through the looking-glass] {{Wayback|url=http://www.npetro.net/resources/opendemocracy.pdf |date=20130731161446 }} [[openDemocracy|openDemocracy]]. "...while only about half of Russian households have a telephone line at home, well over 90% have access to the First Channel and Rossiya. And for a vast majority of Russians, they are virtually the only source of information about political events. Given that typically well over half of their news broadcasts consist of sympathetic coverage of Vladimir Putin and members of the United Russia party, and oppositional figures are always presented in a negative or ironic light (if at all), it is unsurprising that the president is enjoying considerable popularity.". Retrieved 16 April 2008.</ref>。

普京是2007年《[[时代_(杂志)|时代]]》[[年度风云人物|年度风云人物]]<ref>[[Adi_Ignatius|Adi Ignatius]]. [http://www.time.com/time/specials/2007/personoftheyear/article/0,28804,1690753_1690757_1690766,00.html Person of the Year 2007] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/2007/personoftheyear/article/0,28804,1690753_1690757_1690766,00.html |date=20130826130830 }}, [[时代_(杂志)|时代]]</ref>；2008年4月，普京成為[[時代百大人物|時代百大人物]]之一<ref>[[Madeleine_Albright|Albright, Madeleine]]. [http://www.time.com/time/specials/2007/article/0,28804,1733748_1733757_1735578,00.html "Vladimir Putin"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/2007/article/0,28804,1733748_1733757_1735578,00.html |date=20130825134000 }}, ''Time''. Retrieved 1 May 2008.</ref>。

